    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn alterColumnToNullable()
      Changes this column to be nullable.
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn alterColumnTypeToMatchDatamodel()
      Changes the type of this column to match that of the datamodel. Does not affect the nullability of the column.
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn create()
      Throws if: - Column already exists. - Column doesn't exist and doesn't have an associated property (we don't know the type). If column doesn't exist and has an associated property, it will create the column for that property.
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn createAllIndexes()
      Creates all indexes on this column
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn createNonNullableWithInitialValue(Object initialValue)
      Throws if: - Column already exists. - Column doesn't exist and doesn't have an associated property (we don't know the type). - Column is nullable. If column doesn't exist and has an associated property, it will create the column for that property as a non-nullable column with the given initial value. In general, the initial value should be an illegal value. Subsequent update(s) will then populate the column with legal values. An illegal value makes it easier to track down the origin of the value. Care must be taken to ensure the subsequent update(s) cover all cases. We recommend the use of this method over create() for non-nullable columns as this obviates the need to make the new column non-nullable later.
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn drop()
      Drops this column
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn dropAllIndexes()
      Drops all indexes on this column
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn dropForeignKeyIfAny()
      Drops foreign key on this column, if there is one
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn dropStatisticsIfRequiredByDBMS()
      Drops statistics on this column if required by the underlying DBMS
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn rename(String newColumnName)
      Renames the column to the given name
      IBeforeUpgradeColumn updateStatistics()
      Drops statistics on this column if required by the underlying DBMS
